not only works only with the right side of the operator

1 + 2

4 / 3
1.3333333

4 // 3
1

python is case sensitive

In [17]: 'a' == 'A'                                                             
Out[17]: False

types of two operands need to be consistent

In [19]: 'a' + True                                                             
